## Coding Conventions

### PHP (Craft CMS)
- PSR-12; type declarations for parameters and returns
- Custom logic in `modules/`, not in templates

### TypeScript / React (Next.js)
- Strict TypeScript; no `any` type
- Server Components by default; `'use client'` only for interactivity
- Define interfaces for all props and API responses
- Use `async` Server Components for data fetching (no `useEffect` for initial data)

### General
- 2-space indentation for TSX/TS/CSS; 4-space for PHP
- Tailwind utility classes; mobile-first responsive design

## Security Requirements

**Never read, display, or include the contents of these files:**

| Category | Files / Patterns |
|----------|-----------------|
| Environment | `.env`, `.env.*` — `.env.example` is safe |
| Craft config | `config/db.php`, `config/general.php` |
| Keys & certs | `*.key`, `*.pem`, `*.p12`, `*.crt` |
| Credentials | `auth.json`, `credentials.json`, `*service-account*.json` |
| Backups | `storage/backups/`, `.ddev/db_snapshots/` |

**Hard rules:**
- Never expose GraphQL API tokens in frontend code (never use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix for tokens)
- Never modify `vendor/` or Craft core
- CORS must be configured on Craft CMS side

## Important Notes

- GraphQL schema is managed in Craft CMS admin (Settings > GraphQL)
- Use environment variables for API URLs and tokens (server-side only)
- Use `next/image` for all images; never use raw `<img>` tags
- See `CLAUDE.md` for Claude Code-specific workflow skills and the memory system
